text: Neshukay () is a rural locality (an aul) in Ponezhukayskoye Rural Settlement of Teuchezhsky District, the Republic of Adygea, Russia. The population was 911 as of 2018. There are 14 streets. == Geography == The aul is on the left bank of the Marta River, 4 km. north-east from the Ponezhukay aul. == Ethnicity == The aul is inhabited by Russians and Adighes. == References == Category:Rural localities in Teuchezhsky District
title: Neshukay
